English (United States)(en-US): The curtain rises. Applause fills the room.
Korean (South Korea)(ko-KR): 커튼이 열린다. 자, 어서 박수를 쳐.

English (United States)(en-US): The small piece of luck buried in the Vasilopita cake has been waiting.
Korean (South Korea)(ko-KR): 바실로비타 빵에 파묻힌 행운이 목 빠져라 기다리고 있어.

English (United States)(en-US): The one who takes that lucky coin will be the star of the party.
Korean (South Korea)(ko-KR): 행운의 동전을 가지는 자야말로 바로 오늘, 파티의 주인공이야.

English (United States)(en-US): The best gifts are the ones you didn’t see coming, right?
Korean (South Korea)(ko-KR): 예상치 못한 선물이 더욱 강렬한 기쁨을 선사하는 법이잖아?

English (United States)(en-US): The radiant lights, the pounding beat,
the hundreds of eyes tracking your every move.
Korean (South Korea)(ko-KR): 모든 그대의 자취를 기억하는 백 쌍의 눈동자.

English (United States)(en-US): But fate was searching for that one lucky person.
Korean (South Korea)(ko-KR): 하지만 운명은 행운의 주인공을 찾고 있었어.
